   <mods:abstract>Their vessel was seized off the Island of Henecauga by a British customs
            schooner, and is under process of being condemned for illegal trade. Searched earlier
            for foodstuffs, the vessel was allowed 48 hours to leave port. Leaving in less than an
            hour, she met a French vessel, and returned to port to transfer a cargo of sugar, coffee
            cotton and cocoa, at which time she was seized along with the French vessel. Please
            bring this breach of international law to attention of Congress.</mods:abstract>
